The paper proposes a method for automatic brain tumor segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques such as residual connections and multi-scale predictions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on medical imaging and brain tumors may also make the paper relevant to neural engineering (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
